<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" box="[199,519,330,355]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Length of male 3.5–3.7 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
Coloration. Body light yellowish, except middle part of pronotum and scutellum with brownish black; eyes brownish. Face yellowish-brown. Fore wing yellowish, brochosome-field whitish grey (
<figureCitation box="[1135,1251,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[176,1413,195,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[173,1414,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Habitus (dorsal and lateral views) and face. 1 – 4, Farynala dextra sp. nov., 5 – 8, Farynala sinistra sp. nov., 9 – 12, Xaniona falcata sp. nov.. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807925/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1262,1294,403,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">34</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
External features. Crown rounded, coronal suture distinct and not extended to anterior margin of eyes; length of crown less than interocular width, and width of crown slightly less than pronotal width. Face strongly elevated. Transverse impression distinct at near middle of scutellum. Fore wing with 2nd cell largest, 3rd cell subtriangular, stalked with stem short. Hind wing with two crossveins (
<figureCitation box="[787,902,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[176,1413,195,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[173,1414,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Habitus (dorsal and lateral views) and face. 1 – 4, Farynala dextra sp. nov., 5 – 8, Farynala sinistra sp. nov., 9 – 12, Xaniona falcata sp. nov.. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807925/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[914,988,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">34, 35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" box="[199,907,582,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
Abdominal apodemes reaching middle of 5th sternite (
<figureCitation box="[810,894,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
Male genitalia. Anal tube well developed. Lobe of pygofer rectangular in lateral view, shorter than subgenital plate, without process; with inner sclerotic ledge in basal middle part; with large macrosetae near lower margin, and three small stout macrosetae at posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[748,831,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate longer, narrowed gradually towards apex, with rigid macroseta on outside basally, row of short macrosetae along outer margin, and several microsetae arranged on mesal margin; row of short rigid microsetae scattered on outer apex (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1214,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Figs 33, 37</figureCitation>
). Paramere slender, with row of microsetae on outer margin, apex not curved (
<figureCitation box="[871,1016,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Figs 33, 37</figureCitation>
). Connective elongate, sharp-edged triangular (
<figureCitation box="[276,361,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus dorsal apodeme slightly broader than preatrium in lateral view, aedeagal shaft with serrate plates on middle of dorsal margin; with three apical processes, one process straight and pointed dorsad, pair of processes strongly curved laterally to opposite side, crossed preapically, gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1319,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Figs 38–40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1242,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" box="[199,1242,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name refers to the sickle-like apical processes on the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="527" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,978,1003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Huang" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Huang, 2005: 379 Host" authorityYear="2005" box="[754,1124,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xaniona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerina">
<emphasis box="[754,928,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Xaniona cerina</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Huang
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished by the more robust aedeagus, with the shaft distinctly broadened with teeth dorsally on the middle part of the shaft (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,193,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1393,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Xaniona falcata sp. nov. 33, male pygofer, subgenital plate and paramere, lateral view. 34, fore wing. 35, hind wing. 36, abdominal apodemes, ventral view. 37, subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view. 38, aedeagus, ventral view. 39, aedeagus, lateral view. 40, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/807933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="527">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). The number and positions of the aedeagal processes are also different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
